	(226,1,'2015-06-18 15:03:47','2015-06-18 22:03:47','Google employs more than 50,000 people, and around 20,000 people in Mountain View alone, and that means that the logistics of transporting Googlers to work â€“ and to other buildings on and around their campus â€“ is a difficult one indeed.\r\n\r\nIn an attempt to scratch their own itch, Google has developed autonomous vehicles to transport employees around, and has been working with regulators to legalize autonomous vehicles.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/google-autonomous-vehicle.png\" alt=\"google-autonomous-vehicle\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227\" /><figcaption>Google Autonomous Vehicle Concept</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nIn addition to their autonomous vehicle project, Google already offers hundreds of utilitarian (though some call them ugly), colorful bicycles for use on their sprawling campus.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/googlebikes-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"googlebikes\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-228\" /><figcaption>Google Bikes</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nYesterday, Googler Mike Pegg <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/+mikepegg21/posts/WgTJx1J4mk2\" target=\"_blank\">posted an update on Google+</a> about Google\'s new Specialized Turbo ebikes that employees can check out for use on or near the Googleplex:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Signed out an ebike over lunch to transit to another Google campus. So. Much. Fun!! They should be called weeee bikes! :) Got it to a top speed of 26 mph. Had a huge smile on my face after using it!<br><span class=\"right\">â€“ Mike Pegg</span>ï»¿</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/google1-1980.jpg\" alt=\"google1-1980\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-237\" /><figcaption>One of Google\'s Specialized Turbos</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/google2-1440-1024x951.jpg\" alt=\"Google Specialized Turbo\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-238\" /><figcaption>Google\'s Asset Tracking barcode on a Specialized Turbo</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nAccording to Googler <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/116961301915403381264\" target=\"_blank\">Jacob Glick</a>, Google began testing out the Specialized Turbos with employees last year.\r\n\r\nJacob and Mike are hardly alone in their ebike use: Googler <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/106116111304373377701\" target=\"_blank\">Rob Russell</a> replied to Mike\'s post and noted that he\'s been quite happy commuting to the Googleplex on an ebike for the past few months.\r\n\r\nThis report indicates that electric bike usage is growing at a healthy pace at Google\'s headquarters, and Google\'s efforts to increase ebike use on their campus are likely paying dividends in reduced auto traffic, more efficient utilization of parking, and lower greenhouse gas emissions.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/VeniceDash-1024x752.jpg\" alt=\"2014 IZIP E3 Dash at Google Venice\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-240\" /><figcaption>A lone IZIP E3 Dash sits among employee bikes at Google\'s Venice, CA office</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nGoogle is also reportedly <a href=\"https://www.pedegoelectricbikes.com/pedegos-participation-at-googles-earth-day-celebration/\" target=\"_blank\">working with Pedego</a> and other ebike brands to study the use of ebikes on or near their campuses.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/pedegogoogle-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"pedegogoogle\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-229\" /><figcaption>A Pedego electric bike on Google\'s Mountain View campus</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nSource: <a href=\"https://www.seroundtable.com/photos/google-ebike-20451.html\" target=\"_blank\">Google Has An eBike Program - Search Engine Roundtable</a>','Google Rolls Out Ebikes To Their Mountain View Campus','Google\'s fleet of Specialized Turbos, in testing since last year, may now be available to ordinary Googlers.','publish','open','open','','google-rolls-out-ebikes-to-their-mountain-view-campus','','','2015-06-18 15:24:02','2015-06-18 22:24:02','',0,'http://overvolted.com/?p=226',0,'post','',0),
