	(437,1,'2015-09-15 11:59:37','2015-09-15 18:59:37','News travels fast, and news leaks travel even faster.\r\n\r\nThanks to midwest ebike dealer extraordinaire <a href=\"http://www.crazylennysebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crazy Lenny</a>, we now have some previously unseen images and specs for 2016 models of BH\'s Easy Motion ebikes:\r\n\r\n<figure><img alt=\"2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro Jumper 27.5\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/EN906-NitroJumper275-1-1024x664.jpg\" alt=\"EN906-NitroJumper275 (1)\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-106\" />\r\n<figcaption>2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro Jumper 27.5\"</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\n<figure><img alt=\"2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro 29\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/EN706-Nitro29trasera-847x1024.jpg\" alt=\"EN706-Nitro29trasera\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-105\" />\r\n<figcaption>2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro 29\"</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\n<figure><img alt=\"2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro Jet\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/EN516-NitroJetFrontal-1019x1024.jpg\" alt=\"EN516-NitroJetFrontal\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-104\" />\r\n<figcaption>2016 BH Easy Motion Nitro Jet</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\n<figure><img alt=\"2016 BH Easy Motion with Brose Mid-Drive\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/BH-Brose.jpg\" alt=\"BH Brose\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103\" />\r\n<figcaption>2016 BH Easy Motion with Brose Mid-Drive</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nAside from the above photos, we know that the rear hub motors will be pushing out 500W (an increase from the 350W motors that Easy Motion has used in the past), most of the EVO models will sport 48V systems instead of the previous 36V, batteries have seen an increase in capacity to 500 watt-hours, GPS tracking has been enabled by integrating a GPS unit under the battery, and a new 80Nm <a href=\"http://www.brose.com/en/Company/\" target=\"_blank\">Brose</a> mid-drive motor is now powering all of the Easy Motion off-road models.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.emotionbikesusa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Easy Motion</a> doesn\'t seem to be too concerned about making a splash with product announcements lately, with <a href=\"http://www.emotionbikesusa.com/news/article/10\" target=\"_blank\">their last update to their news section</a> being made in September 2014 when they announced their 2015 model line at <a href=\"http://www.interbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Interbike</a>, but this may point to a possible roll-out at <a href=\"http://www.interbike.com/show-info.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Interbike 2015</a>, so we imagine we\'ll be hearing more from Easy Motion about the new models in September.\r\n\r\nThough the new models are not available for ordering yet, we imagine that Crazy Lenny will be stocking them soon enough <a href=\"http://www.crazylennysebikes.com/easy-motion.html\" target=\"_blank\">right here</a>. Feel free to join the discussion thread about the news leak over at <a href=\"http://electricbikereview.com/community/threads/2016-models-from-bh-just-a-preview.2072/\" target=\"_blank\">Electric Bike Review\'s Community forum</a>.','2016 BH Easy Motion Models Leaked','News travels fast, and news leaks travel even faster. Today, a trove of BH Easy Motion\'s 2016 models has leaked. Read on to find out more.','inherit','closed','closed','','102-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 11:59:37','2015-09-15 18:59:37','',102,'http://overvolted.com/102-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(438,1,'2015-09-15 12:05:45','2015-09-15 19:05:45','Eurobike and Interbike are the two major bicycle industry tradeshows that occur each fall, and these two tradeshows are where the majority of big product announcements are made.\r\n\r\nGiven that Eurobike has passed, Interbike offers a chance to see what products will make it to the US market. Haibike and BH Easy Motion have announced a plethora of new products at Eurobike, but not all of them will make their way to our fair shores.\r\n\r\nHere\'s a rundown of what we can expect to find out at this year\'s Interbike, which is happening this week:\r\n\r\n<strong>Haibike brings off-road focused SDURO ebikes stateside</strong>\r\n\r\nHaibike has long sold its less-expensive SDURO line (which are powered by Yamaha electric systems) in Europe, but only brought their more expensive Bosch-powered XDURO line to the US. <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/haibike-bringing-yamaha-powered-sduro-line-to-the-us/\" target=\"_blank\">That is changing in 2016</a>. It\'s not clear if Haibike\'s current US marketing and distribution partner (Currie Tech/Accel North America) will be handling the SDURO introduction, but the language coming from press releases seems to indicate that Accel North America will only handle XDURO imports. If true, this could mean that it might be more difficult to find the new SDURO bikes in the US come 2016, or that SDURO Haibikes and XDURO Haibikes will be found at different dealers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Vintage Electric Bikes to add front suspension option</strong>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-version=\"4\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:8px;\"> <div style=\" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:33.4259259259% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;\"> <div style=\" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;\"></div></div><p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\"><a href=\"https://instagram.com/p/7ij6nBN4Gv/\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_top\">A photo posted by Vintage Electric Bikes (@vintageelectric)</a> on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2015-09-12T18:07:17+00:00\">Sep 12, 2015 at 11:07am PDT</time></p></div></blockquote>\r\n<script async defer src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vintageelectricbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Vintage Electric Bikes</a>, purveyor of the retro-styled E-Tracker and Cruz models, is finally equipping one of its steeds with a front suspension fork, which will go to good use, as both their models sport top speeds of 36MPH, and hitting a pothole at those speeds without any dampening could be very dangerous.\r\n\r\n<strong>Pedego Launches its first mountain bike</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.pedegoelectricbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Pedego</a>, which has seemed to limit itself to casual cruiser and around-town bikes, has introduced <a href=\"http://www.pedegoelectricbikes.com/shop/ridge-rider/\" target=\"_blank\">its first electric mountain bike, the Ridge Rider</a>.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/pedego-ridge-rider.jpg\" alt=\"2016 Pedego Ridge Rider\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-432\" /><figcaption>The 2016 Pedego Ridge Rider</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nThe Ridge Rider\'s offers a 500-watt geared motor which seems to be beefy enough to ascend the steepest climbs, and is powered by a 48-volt, 11 amp hour battery. Its components seem to be ready to meet any challenge, with its Suntour XCR Air 27.5 suspension with 100mm travel and Magura front and rear hydraulic disc brakes. The bike offers only a front suspension option, which means that for serious trail freaks, this bike is likely already out of the question, but for current Pedego owners who want their bikes to see a little trail action from time to time, the Ridge Rider could be a great option.\r\n\r\n<strong>28MPH S-pedelecs from Haibike XDURO</strong>\r\n\r\nThe majority of Haibike XDURO\'s line available in the US has been limited to 20MPH, whereas competitors like Stromer, Easy Motion, and IZIP have long offered bikes sporting top speeds in excess of 25MPH. In 2016, Haibike will offer more 28MPH-capable ebikes in order to better compete in the marketplace.\r\n\r\n<strong>The 2016 Stromer ST2 and ST2-S</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://overvolted.com/the-2016-stromer-st2-and-st2-s/\" target=\"_blank\">The 2016 Stromer ST2-S</a> was announced at Eurobike, and it will likely make its US debut at Interbike.\r\n\r\n<strong>Updated E3 Dash and E3 ProDrive from IZIP</strong>\r\n\r\nIZIP\'s new <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-izip-e3-protour/\" target=\"_blank\">2016 E3 ProTour</a> will likely make its US debut alongside the new <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/the-2016-izip-e3-dash/\" target=\"_blank\">2016 IZIP E3 Dash</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>2016 Specialized Turbo and Turbo S</strong>\r\n\r\nSpecialized is the kind of brand with such an intense following that it can skip Interbike entirely and still get bike dealers and the media to show up to its new model year kickoff events, and that is indeed what\'s happening this year. Just because <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/the-2016-specialized-turbo/\" target=\"_blank\">the new Turbo</a> won\'t be at Interbike doesn\'t mean that it won\'t be a force to be reckoned with come 2016.\r\n\r\n<strong>2016 Bosch Ebike Product Updates</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bosch-ebike-product-updates/\" target=\"_blank\">Bosch has made some major announcements for 2016</a>, including <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bosch-ebike-product-updates/\" target=\"_blank\">a larger 500Wh battery</a> and a torquier <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bosch-ebike-product-updates/\" target=\"_blank\">75Nm Performance Line CX mid-drive motor</a> that is poised to be a big seller on electric mountain bikes. The rumor is that the new 500Wh battery isn\'t coming to the US just yet, as it needs to pass regulatory approval, but Bosch will likely be bringing some very exciting tech to the US, including its <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bosch-ebike-product-updates/\" target=\"_blank\">eShift system</a>, which offers automatic shifting in concert with systems from Shimano Alfine Di2, SRAM, and Nuvinci.\r\n\r\n<strong>New products from BH Easy Motion</strong>\r\n\r\nEasy Motion announced dozens of new and updated models at Eurobike, but unfortunately, only some of them are going to make the trip across the pond. Look out for 500W drives, 48V systems replacing 36V ones, new <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bh-easy-motion-models-leaked/\" target=\"_blank\">Brose mid-drives</a>, and the <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/2016-bh-easy-motion-models-leaked/\" target=\"_blank\">new REVO</a> line.','What To Expect From Interbike','Want to get a sneak peak of what announcements are to come at this week\'s Interbike tradeshow? We\'ve got the scoop.','inherit','closed','closed','','431-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 12:05:45','2015-09-15 19:05:45','',431,'http://overvolted.com/431-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(439,1,'2015-09-15 14:09:58','2015-09-15 21:09:58','<img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/sale.png\" alt=\"sale\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-361\" />\r\n\r\nNew bicycle models tend to be announced in the early fall and launch the following spring, and most bike sales occur in the spring or summer, and as a result, bike shops tend to try and get rid of extra inventory in the fall so that they can make room for inventory from the following model year, and luckily for ebike buyers, this year is no exception.\r\n\r\nRight now, <a href=\"http://www.electricbikeseattle.com/blogs/bike-blog/46730565-fire-sale-pricing-list\" target=\"_blank\">Seattle Electric Bike is holding a fire sale</a> (<a href=\"http://overvolted.com/fire-at-seattle-e-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">literally</a>), with deals on IZIP, Stealth, ProdecoTech, Vanmoof, Focus, Polaris, and more, with discounts from 10%-50% off retail.\r\n\r\nThe midwest\'s very well known high volume retailer, <a href=\"http://www.crazylennysebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crazy Lenny\'s Ebikes</a>, has an ongoing sale on 2014 models:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2014 IZIP E3 Dash or the 2014 IZIP E3 Peak <strong>$1,580</strong></li>\r\n	<li>2014 Easy Motion Neo Cross <strong>$1,580</strong>, 2014 Neo Jumper <strong>$1,990</strong></li>\r\n	<li>2014 Stromer ST1 Elite <strong>$1,980</strong>, 2014 Haibike 29er <strong>$2,200</strong></li>\r\n	<li>EG brand ebikes <strong>$750-900</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nCrazy Lenny\'s Ebikes held a big warehouse sale in May with prices on Stromer ST1s as low as $1,900 (nearly 50% off retail!), Easy Motion ebikes like the Neo Cross for $1,480, and Schwinn Tailwinds for less than $500. That sale only went on for about a week, but savvy shoppers might be able to negotiate similar deals today.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/propel.png\" alt=\"propel\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-362\" />\r\n\r\nMajor northeast retailer Propel is having a sale on certain models from <a href=\"http://propelbikes.com/IZIP-electric-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">IZIP</a>, <a href=\"http://propelbikes.com/easy-motion-electric-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Easy Motion</a>, <a href=\"http://propelbikes.com/raleigh-en\" target=\"_blank\">Raleign</a>, <a href=\"http://propelbikes.com/specialized-en\" target=\"_blank\">Specialized</a>, and more, with some models selling for more than 20%-off of retail price.\r\n\r\nBH Easy Motion is offering <a href=\"http://www.emotionbikesusa.com/docs/EM-Coupon-v3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">a coupon for $500 off its Evo Jet and Evo Street models</a> until September 30th, 2015.\r\n\r\nHave you heard of any good sales that you\'d like to share with the ebike community? <a href=\"http://overvolted.com/contact/\" target=\"_blank\">Drop us a line and let us know</a>!','End Of Season Ebike Sales','It\'s end-of-season sales time. We\'ve got you covered when it comes to who\'s got discounts on what.','inherit','closed','closed','','360-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 14:09:58','2015-09-15 21:09:58','',360,'http://overvolted.com/360-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(441,1,'2015-09-16 16:18:30','2015-09-16 23:18:30','Interbike offers quite a bit of excitement and the chance to ride just about every ebike under one roof. However, since Eurobike just happened a few weeks back, few product announcements were saved for Interbike, with the surprising result being that the most exciting ebike news this week came from the usually staid folks at Pedego, whose new Ridge Rider electric mountain bike is not only full of quality parts, but accelerates faster than just about any other ebike at the show.\r\n\r\nHere\'s our day one photo gallery, with a few pre-show shots from Tuesday thrown in for good measure:\r\n\r\n[gallery ids=\"496,486,445,541,540,539,538,537,536,535,534,533,532,531,530,529,528,527,526,525,522,521,519,518,516,515,514,513,512,511,510,509,508,507,506,505,504,503,502,501,499,498,497,494,493,492,491,489,488,487\"]','Interbike Day 1 - Electric Bike Photos','Day 1 of Interbike gave few surprises, but the ebike industry has made quite the showing this year.','publish','open','open','','interbike-day-1-electric-bike-photos','','','2015-09-16 16:18:30','2015-09-16 23:18:30','',0,'http://overvolted.com/?p=441',0,'post','',3),
