	(621,1,'2015-09-24 11:33:27','2015-09-24 18:33:27','Did you think you got a lot of air on that high-speed singletrack jump? You\'ve got nothing on Freddy Nock!\n\nThe Swiss daredevil is well known for his Guiness World Record tightrope walk through the alps, but now he\'s brought his exploits to the shores of Lake Zurich atop a Stromer electric bike!\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-612\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockerlenbachSPF_1.jpg\" alt=\"nockerlenbachSPF_1\" />\n\nThe tightrope was 485 meters long, and ran from Erlenbach\'s church tower all the way to its train station.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-613\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockerlenbachSPF_2.jpg\" alt=\"nockerlenbachSPF_2\" />\n\nThe tightrope route\'s difficulty was compounded by the fact that it ran uphill, at an average 3.7% grade.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-614\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockerlenbachSPF_3.jpg\" alt=\"nockerlenbachSPF_3\" />\n\nFreddy Nock won two Guiness World Records, one for the longest tightripe bike ride, and one for the steepest tightrope bike ride ascent.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-615\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockweltrekorderlenbach010.jpg\" alt=\"nockweltrekorderlenbach010\" />\n\nNock trained for this record-breaking attempt for five years.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-616\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockweltrekorderlenbach012.jpg\" alt=\"nockweltrekorderlenbach012\" />\n\nThe record attempt occurred above a large streetfair called Erlenbacher Chilbi.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-617\" src=\"http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/nockweltrekorderlenbach013.jpg\" alt=\"nockweltrekorderlenbach013\" />','Swiss Daredevil Freddy Nock Rides Stromer Electric Bike On A Tightrope For Guiness World Record','','inherit'